@startuml ct_data_wire_log
' ============================================================
' Title:     nasim — Wire Log Data Structures
' Boundary:  nasim code agent CLI
' Purpose:   Data models for append-only wire event store
' Milestone: v1.0
' Version:   1.0.0
' Source:    docs/audit/audit_2026-06-20_capability-and-architecture.md
' Review:    —
' Note:      Append-only — events are never updated or deleted.
'            Physical storage: ~/.nasim/sessions/<id>/wire.jsonl
' ============================================================

title nasim — Wire Log Data Structures

skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0

package "Wire Log Data" #E3F2FD {

    class WireEvent <<dataclass>> {
        + session_id : str
        + sequence : int
        + event_type : str
        + turn_number : int
        + timestamp : str
        + payload : dict
        + byte_offset : int
    }

    class TurnIndexEntry <<dataclass>> {
        + turn_number : int
        + byte_offset : int
        + timestamp : str
    }

    class WireMetadata <<dataclass>> {
        + session_id : str
        + total_events : int
        + total_turns : int
        + created_at : str
    }
}

note bottom of WireEvent
  Each event is a single JSON line in wire.jsonl.
  byte_offset enables efficient seeking for replay.
  sequence is monotonically increasing within session.
end note

note bottom of TurnIndexEntry
  Provides O(1) jump to a specific turn's byte position.
  Enables fast partial replay and session forking.
end note

note right of WireMetadata
  Written as first line of wire.jsonl.
  Updated on session close with final counts.
end note

@enduml
